articles.description: Steven Haney scored a career-best 31 points and Loyola Marymount held on for an 85-79 win over Pepperdine on Saturday afternoon, snapping a three-game skid.
articles.headline: Loyola Marymount holds on for 85-79 win over Pepperdine

articles.description: Nick King matched his career-high with 32 points, tying the school record with his fourth 30-point game this season, and Middle Tennessee held off North Texas 79-73 to win its seventh straight on Saturday.
articles.headline: King scores 32, MTSU holds off North Texas 79-73

articles.description: Kevin Brown and John Thompson III break down Wichita State's win over UConn and the tough schedule ahead for the Shockers.
articles.headline: Thompson: This is the Wichita State team we've been looking for

images.caption: Kevin Brown and John Thompson III break down Wichita State's win over UConn and the tough schedule ahead for the Shockers.
images.name: Thompson: This is the Wichita State team we've been looking for

articles.description: Jordy Kuiper scored 12 points, James Dickey had 11 points and nine rebounds, and UNC Greensboro beat Western Carolina 65-48 on Saturday.
articles.headline: UNC Greensboro keeps pace with ETSU, beats Western Carolina

articles.description: After edging No. 3 Purdue earlier in the week, No. 14 Ohio State cruises to an 82-64 win against Iowa.
articles.headline: Ohio State rolls against Iowa

images.caption: After edging No. 3 Purdue earlier in the week, No. 14 Ohio State cruises to an 82-64 win against Iowa.
images.name: Ohio State rolls against Iowa

articles.description: Keita Bates-Diop had 14 points and eight rebounds, and No. 14 Ohio State beat Iowa 82-64 on Saturday for sole possession of first place in the Big Ten.
articles.headline: No. 14 Ohio State drops Iowa 82-64, takes Big Ten lead
